sentences: Sarah Champion (born 1970 in Manchester) is an English music journalist and author.
She has documented the 24 Hour Party People era and edited several collections of chemical fiction, including Disco Biscuits in 1997.
In the 1990s, Champion edited four anthologies of fiction for Sceptre and Penguin which were accompanied by CD releases and club nights.
This was followed by Disco 2000 — a book about pre-millennial paranoia, Shenanigans — about Ireland after dark, and Fortune Hotel — a collection of twisted travel stories).
In 2004, she was mistaken for the blogging prostitute Belle de Jour.
In June 2006 she moved back to London.
In August 2006 she wrote a cover story for The Observer's Review section about the return of rave culture.
Rave article by Sarah Champion in The Observer, 27 August 2006
